Europe is suffering from extremely high temperatures. Spain's meteorological agency says both Spain and Portugal experienced their second heatwave in a month, with scorching temperatures expected in France and the UK in the coming days.  People in Spain sweltered with the town of Candeleda registering an eye-watering 43.3 ℃ shortly after 6 p.m. The UK issued an extreme heat warning, with temperatures predicted to go over 30℃ across large parts of England and Wales.